May 25 2009 	Adequate	This hotel is very shabby, but the location is fantastic. If you get a good rate on line, it's worth a stay. It has a decent little pool and exercise room. I've never eaten in the restaurant - why would you when you are in Montreal, a diner's paradise!? There's a great coffee shop two blocks away for breakfast. There is an entrance to the metro in the hotel, or you can walk 2 or 3 blocks down the hill to the central metro station for the whole city. The staff are friendly. The hotel is convenient to tourist and cultural sites, and is also close to downtown. It just desperately needs an update but if you're ok with tired decor, there's no reason not to stay here. And by the way the views are incredible. One downside: I did have a lot of problems with the wifi ... although it was free! It dropped a lot.	
