Nov 2 2008 	Faded beauty- Honest yet shows its age	Booked this through Priceline for 82$ all inclusive. As one of the previous reviewer mentioned, as the Canadian dollar is going down, it may be worthwhile to check the Hilton website directly, which is in CA$. We arrived late. When I called in the morning, they told me only rooms with doubles where available, however, I was given a King upon request. Service was friendly. The hotel was very busy on this Halloween evening. The room itself was clean, spacious, with a very comfortable king bed and pillows which were not overtly soft. The bathroom is diminutive and the shower is anaemic at best, and rather dirty, due to the anti-slip covering on the floor of the bath. Toiletries are adequate. The view from the room on the 18th was quite nice, overseeing the Champlain bridge and the river. The exercise room is equipped with TV mounted aerobic machines. The pool is of decent size, however, the walls were peeling and moulding. The sauna is in each of the men and ladies room, and barely worked in both, I understand. Parking is expensive, but you can park on St-Hubert, and streets further east, or its 7 to 10$ for 24h at the Bibliothèque Nationale. Metro is very close (Sherbrooke Station). Restaurant is expensive for breakfast, so I recommend L'Évidence on St-Denis and Cherrier (4.99$ for 2 eggs, 2 pancakes, potatoes, fruits, and toasts, with maple syrup!).Overall, a decent hotel showing some signs of wear and in need of a good refurbishing.	
