Aug 29 2008 	Interesting stay	I stayed at the Doubletree for two nights. The location was much better and more convienent than I had thought it would be when I booked it. It was just around the corner from the Metro stop that can take you to the eating and shopping areas in Montreal.The bathroom needed updating, but was adequate for our needs. We had a north facing room and we didn't hear a single other guest while we were in the rooms. We had two confusing occurences happen to us. The first was when our keycards became demagnetized after being in a pocket of my purse all day. According to the girl at the desk this happens when the cards come into close proximity to credit cards or a magnet. She quickly reactivated them and we were able to enter our room. The second came when our bill reflected a charge for phone calls that were made before we had checked into our room. This was also corrected quickly at check-out. Overall, a nice stay and I would stay there again if only for the close proximity to public transportation and the view.	
